      • addDefaultPrefixModule

        default CommandModuleBuilder addDefaultPrefixModule(java.lang.String prefix)
        This adds a module that implements PrefixModule to provide a static prefix that cannot be changed. If a PrefixModule is not added, one will be provided with a static prefix of "!"

        This method's implementation is: 

         addModule(new DefaultPrefixModule(prefix))

        You can define a different prefix implementation by providing an object to addModule(ICommandModule) that implements IPrefixModule

        Parameters:
        prefix - a string the defines a global prefix
        Returns:
        this

      • addDefaultAdminModule

        default CommandModuleBuilder addDefaultAdminModule()
        This enables the @Admin annotation that is marked on Command classes. This ensures that Commands marked with @Admin are only usable by Administrators.

        It is important to include an implementation of AdminModule through either this method, BreadBotClientBuilder.addAdminModule(Predicate), or your own implementation. Otherwise, all users will have access to Administrative Commands

        The default criteria for defining an Administrator is as follows:

        • Has Kick Members Permission
        • Is higher than the bot on the role hierarchy

        Different criteria to determine which member has administrative status with BreadBotClientBuilder.addAdminModule(Predicate) or your own implementation of AdminModule

        Returns:
        this

      • addAdminModule

        default CommandModuleBuilder addAdminModule(java.util.function.Predicate<net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.Member> isAdmin)
        Define custom behavior to determine which members can use Commands marked with @Admin
